args:
Drawn by a mysterious letter, Jupiter and the
party come to a town overrun with imperial
soldiers and find Eryn, a girl who's been forced
into a court case that seems impossible to win.
Unable to stand such a travesty of justice,
Jupiter decides to become her lawyer.

Dear Prince {player_name},
I place the last of my hopes with you.
Please, come rescue me!

—A citizen of Littleton
This is the letter we received earlier.\nThoughts, anyone?
That thing's fishier than a cat's breakfast.\nIf they really want our help, maybe they\nshould tell us what the heck's going on!

I suppose it could be. But on the other
hand, what if someone DOES need help?
It would be wrong to abandon them just
because we're suspicious.
But that being said, I've never even heard\nof ＂Littleton.＂ Are we sure the place exists?
Littleton is a small town on the\nnorthern border.
Being on the border, it's tied quite closely\nto the Ilian Church—which likely explains\nwhy it's such a peaceful, sleepy burg.
Oh, and I HIGHLY recommend the corn.\nIt's their specialty.
Okay, who is this guy, and why is he\nso freakin' SHINY?!
So dazzling... I can't look away!
You don't recognize this adorable face?\nIt's me! Jupiter! ...The Lightwyrm?
Jupiter?! When did you take human form?!

Oh, I slipped into this little number the
moment I heard the name Littleton.
A dragon's got to get nice and gussied up
if he wants to visit there!
Turns out there's a certain something that\nties me to that place, which means I have\nno intention of ignoring that letter.
Dude. I mean, hang on. Just...\nThat letter is LOADED with red flags!

Very much aware, but not concerned.
If we get there and it's real, we help. 
If we get there and it's fake, we do a bit
of sightseeing and skedaddle on home.
Sleepy little Littleton is the perfect place\nfor some R&R—and if I may be so bold,\nwe could all use it. So what do you say?
Well, if Jupiter knows this place and wants\nto check it out, I see no reason not to.
A Few Days Later\nLittleton's Main Street
WOOOOO! This town is the BEST!\nWe can do whatever the hell we want,\nso I say we par-tay doooooown!
Those imperial soldiers certainly seem to\nbe having a good time. Which is, uh...\nI mean, that's strange, right?
Strange. Weird. Weirdly strange. All of it.\nThis is a quiet and gentle little town,\nnot some vulgar den of villainy.

This used to be a peaceful paradise where
fields of corn swayed in the gentle breeze.
...And now that I think of it, what are
imperial soldiers even DOING here?
I'm not sure. Normally the Empire's\ninfluence weakens as you get closer\nto the border.

Yo yo yo! I smell me a traitor!
A nasty traitor prince!
And even looking at his face
just makes me want to wince!
They've spotted us! And, uh...\nI think they're trying to rap?

Someone sent a letter!
It might have been hot air!
But he came runnin' just to help
because he's such a square!

Thank you, princely sir!
You really made our day!
Now get your booty over here
and we'll lock it away!
Gya! They've surrounded us! Jupiter,\nlend me your strength and we'll cut\na path out of—

Now where you think you're going?
You can't just run away!
You're worth a million shiny rupees,
and someone's gonna PAY!
My, my. Quite the show of skill there.\nI suppose I should go save him, buuut...\nOh, he'll be fine.
I have more important things to do—\nsuch as figuring out why this town\nhas suddenly gone bananas!
Well, I thought I'd discover something,\nbut all found on my little walkabout\nwere those weird imperial soldiers.
I'd love to talk to some actual residents,\nbut... Hmm? I say, what have we here?
Oh, this can't be happening! Now SHE'S\na victim of that terrible prosecutor?!
This spells the end of the village. Nobody\ncan beat that prosecutor—especially since\nhe has the support of the imperial soldiers.
What's this about a prosecutor and some\nsoldiers, and why is everyone looking so\nforlornly at that bulletin board posting?
Sorry to intrude, but do your current\nmournful looks have something to do\nwith the imperials posted about town?

You must be new, traveler—our town's
been like this for some time now. Sadly,
the town prosecutor bought off all of
those imperial scoundrels.
That would seem to exceed his purview.\nWhy doesn't your mayor step in?

The prosecutor IS the mayor now.
Nobody wanted it, but we can't oppose
him unless we want to get trampled
under his boot.

If you so much as blink the wrong way,
he'll drag you to court and make sure
you lose the shirt off your back and the
pants off your behind.

A few people raised their voices against
his violent ways, but the moment they lost
in court, we never saw 'em again.
He's evil, I tells ya! Evil to the core!
And his mansion is so closely guarded,\neven the Templars tasked with protecting\nour fair city can't pin any crimes on him.
That sounds simply terrible. You'd think\nit would spark the fire of rebellion in at\nleast someone.
Is that what happened with the woman\nyou were discussing earlier?

Aye, she tried to resist the prosecutor,
but now she's been arrested by the
imperials and dragged off to prison 
like all the rest. Poor child...
Yes, poor child indeed. Off topic,\nbut where is this prison located?

It's a building just a ways north of here,
but why would you ask such a thing,
stranger? It's locked up tight as a drum,
and no good will come of your being there.
Why else? I'm going to ask them to look\nthe other way while I stroll right in.
YEAAAAAAAH! I can't feel my anything!
There there. There's a good boy.\nNow then, where is that young miss?
I can't believe this! How could you let\nyourself get arrested?! Now it's all over!

Er, please try to remain calm! This town
has been a lot to take in, and I'm still a
little confused. Uh, I'm sorry for getting
captured...
Sounds like she's just down that way.\nBut who is that other voice, mmm?
Ah-ha! I knew it. The Prince is here.\nTsk tsk, you two! No talking among\nprisoners! Keep to your own cells!

Jupiter?! Oh, I am SO glad to see you!
Listen, the woman in the cell next to me
is named Eryn, and she's apparently the
former mayor's daughter.
She was about to take a stand against the\ncurrent mayor, so he set her up and had\nher locked away.

He's trying to frame me for MURDER,
the cad! He knows I have a key I won't
let out of my sight, so now he's taking
drastic measures to acquire it.

If he has me found guilty, the key is his—
and then he'll try to open the sacred
treasure! Ooo, I can't WAIT to take that
big jerk to court!
A bit late for that, seeing as he's already\ntaking you there.

Still, you're clearly who the townsfolk were
speaking of. The daughter of the former
mayor? One beloved by all? There can't be
a bigger target for a crooked prosecutor.
Though normally, I'd expect him to target\nthe former mayor and not his daughter.
My father died in prison—which is why I\nhave to protect this key with my life!

Oh dear. My apologies. Perhaps we'd best
change topics: What key are we talking
about, and what is this sacred treasure
you so cryptically mentioned?
It's apparently a box filled with relics from\nKing Alberius, and she has the only key.

The one and only! It's a family heirloom
passed down from generation to
generation. He gave it to us personally and
said it would grant power and prosperity.
That jerk of a prosecutor stole it from us\nwhen he took my father out of power.
But he still can't open it without the key—\nand even if he DID get the key,\nthat still wouldn't be enough.

In order to open it, you have to have
dragonblood, which is something only
royals have. Oh, you should have seen his
face get all pouty when I told him that!
Which explains the letter we received.\nHeavens, this all actually WAS a trap?\nI can't believe Luca was right.
Yes, it seems the prosecutor wants\nthose relics no matter the cost.

And if we do nothing, he's clearly going to
charge you with some random crime.
Trespassing or jaywalking or spitting
into the wind or what have you.
Then he'll railroad you into a sham guilty \nverdict and presto! Your life is over.

As ridiculous as it seems, I think that's
just what's going on in this town now.
It also explains why they have hardly any
defense attorneys.

Well, nobody wants to fight an
unwinnable battle. I take it this
means you still haven't attained
legal representation, miss?
No, but so what? I don't need some\npuffy-wig-wearing stuffed shirt to give\nthat stupid prosecutor what for!

Bad enough some thief broke into my
place before, but now I'm framed for
MURDER?! Oh, he will not get away
with this. He will NOT.
So I'm gonna represent myself,\nget acquitted, and then SUE THE HECK\nOUTTA THAT SCUMBAG RATFINK!
So even if it hurts, you still don't want to\ngo down without a fight?
In that case, you have my help.
I, Jupiter, will be your defense attorney!

I'll glamorously win that court case,
expose the scummy prosecutor for who
he is, and get you two AND your prized
possession back in one fell swoop!
